          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Visual and interaction guidelines to ensure avatars are effective, consistent, and accessible.</p>
          <div class="do-dont-grid">
            <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Provide alt text:</strong> Always include alt or aria-label with the user's full name for image avatars.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Use fallback chain:</strong> Attempt Image first, then Initials, then Placeholder Icon for graceful degradation.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Keep sizes consistent:</strong> Use the same avatar size within lists, tables, and repeated UI contexts.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Pair with name:</strong> In most contexts, display the user's name alongside the avatar for clarity.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>No long initials:</strong> Don't use more than 2 characters for initials.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>No deformed images:</strong> Don't stretch, squish, or crop images in non-uniform ways.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>No misused Hover type:</strong> Don't show the Hover overlay in read-only or non-editable contexts.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>No sole identification:</strong> Don't use avatars as the only way to identify users in critical workflows.</li>
              </ul>
